President Obama spoke with Republic of Korea President Lee Myung-bak to discuss and coordinate a response to North Korea's nuclear test. They both condemned the test and agreed to work together, including at the United Nations Security Council, to impede North Korea's nuclear and ballistic missile programs and reduce the risk of proliferation. President Obama reaffirmed the United States' defense commitments to South Korea and thanked President Lee for his leadership and friendship. He also pledged to work closely with President-elect Park to strengthen U.S.-ROK cooperation.